article.headline: MVSU 93, Dillard 66
article.story: ct/strngr ITTA BENA, Miss. (AP) -- Chris Watson had 24 points and 13 rebounds in his first game for Mississippi Valley State and the Delta Devils beat Dillard 93-66 on Friday night. Watson hit 9 of 12 field goals and 6 of 7 free throws to help MVSU (2-8) earn its second straight win after opening the season with eight consecutive losses. Michael Clark scored 15 for the Delta Devils and Carl Lucas added 13. Kenyon Harper led the Dillard (4-5) with 13 points and Sam Givens and Cornice Wingate had 11 apiece.
